{
  "texts": [
    "LLMs are prone to hallucinations, which could impact decision reliability.",
    "To mitigate this, future iterations will integrate rule-based checks and domain-specific constraints, as well as feedback loops from medical experts, to improve the system's robustness and decision accuracy in high-stakes environments.",
    "Gathering insights from medical professionals will also help assess the LLM's alignment with expert-defined surgical priorities, refining its adaptability to clinical needs.",
    "Safety in surgical tasks is essential, and the current framework will be expanded to address this by incorporating force-based thresholds to control tool speed and acceleration, collision detection, and Safe Reinforcement Learning (Safe RL) techniques, such as reward shaping and risk-sensitive policies, to enhance safe tool proximity to sensitive tissues.",
    "Additionally, to better handle dynamic scenarios, future work will explore mid-sequence task re-planning to adapt to external disturbances and refine LLM reasoning capabilities through reinforcement learning from human feedback, ultimately improving the framework's scalability to other surgical and medical tasks."
  ]
}